notesStmt.note: 298 leaves foliated 1-298, upper left and lower right verso.
Single wooden board with beveled edges supports the manuscript; the board has writing on it, such as a mantra dedicated to the deity Gaṇeśa.
Mistakes blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout; vertical margins marked with quadruple black line.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Manuscript is a grammatical treatise and part of a super-commentary on the Siddhāntakaumudī by Bhaṭṭojī Dīkṣita.
